Apostle Johnson Suleman of the Omega Fire Ministries, Auchi, Edo State, has reacted to Arsenal’s latest Premier League 3-1 victory over Manchester United. DAILY POST reports that Arsenal defeated Man United following goals from Nuno Taveres, Bukayo Saka and Granit Xhaka. Cristiano Ronaldo did score for Ralf Rangnick’s men at Emirates. Reacting, Suleman hailed Arsenal for playing a beautiful game of football against Man United. He also lauded Arsenal manager, Mikel Arteta for a nice work done against the Red Devils. In a tweet via his Twitter handle, Sulema, a passionate Arsenal fan, wrote: “Arsenal 3-1 Man united. Beautiful game of football. “Man U fans no worry..ETH will try next season. Nice work from Arteta and the boys!” Arsenal’s next game is against West Ham United next Sunday.